1
00:00:11,160 --> 00:00:13,600
Okay, so tell me you have a plan.

2
00:00:13,680 --> 00:00:15,440
Hey? Why do I have to have a plan?

3
00:00:15,520 --> 00:00:17,520
You could have a plan.
I chose the restaurant.

4
00:00:17,600 --> 00:00:20,120
Yes, and accidentally took us
to the planet of the Rain Gods,

5
00:00:20,200 --> 00:00:21,840
where we are now being sacrificed.

6
00:00:21,920 --> 00:00:23,760
-Plan!
-Okay.

7
00:00:23,840 --> 00:00:26,600
The plan is we need to distract them
with something

8
00:00:26,680 --> 00:00:28,840
before they actually sacrifice
us to the Rain Gods.

9
00:00:28,920 --> 00:00:31,680
Then when they're distracted,
we run away.

10
00:00:31,760 --> 00:00:33,360
That's not a plan, that's just hoping.

11
00:00:33,440 --> 00:00:36,800
Hey, it's a start.
Can you smell something?

12
00:00:36,880 --> 00:00:38,360
Why are they sacrificing us
to the Rain Gods, anyway?

13
00:00:38,440 --> 00:00:40,040
Appeases their wrath.

14
00:00:40,160 --> 00:00:43,480
Apparently, it's very good
for the crops, you know, sacrificing.

15
00:00:43,560 --> 00:00:45,280
There is actually
some scientific evidence...

16
00:00:45,360 --> 00:00:47,400
Oh, so you're in favour of
being burnt alive now?

17
00:00:47,480 --> 00:00:49,760
Just looking on the bright side, dear.

18
00:00:49,840 --> 00:00:51,560
-(THUNDER ROARS)
-Huh!

19
00:00:51,640 --> 00:00:53,640
Ha, ha! And there it is! Oi!

20
00:00:53,720 --> 00:00:57,360
If there are any Rain Gods up there,
you're rubbish!

21
00:00:57,960 --> 00:01:00,280
Strike me dead if I'm wrong!

22
00:01:00,360 --> 00:01:01,400
What are you doing?

23
00:01:01,480 --> 00:01:02,480
Smelling the ozone, dear.

24
00:01:02,560 --> 00:01:03,720
-(THUNDER CRASHING)
-Down!

25
00:01:05,080 --> 00:01:06,720
-Oh dear.
-Sweetie...

26
00:01:09,360 --> 00:01:12,120
(LAUGHING) Hey!

27
00:01:12,200 --> 00:01:14,880
River, run. Run away!

28
00:01:14,960 --> 00:01:17,480
I think the Rain Gods are going to
do that again, you know.

29
00:01:20,240 --> 00:01:22,080
RIVER: That was your plan?
DOCTOR: Well, it worked, didn't it?

30
00:01:22,160 --> 00:01:23,800
RIVER: Basically, you hoped
for lightning, that was it.

31
00:01:23,880 --> 00:01:24,920
DOCTOR: And here we are.

32
00:01:25,000 --> 00:01:26,440
RIVER: We should be burning
at the stake right now.

33
00:01:26,520 --> 00:01:28,120
It's lucky for you you're pretty.

34
00:01:28,200 --> 00:01:30,320
DOCTOR: You were in no danger.
I knew something would come up.

35
00:01:30,400 --> 00:01:33,480
RIVER: No, you didn't.
DOCTOR: I did! I promise I did.

